July 03, 2020

Temporal Discounting Social Distancing Study 2

Age distribution

The sample ranged in age from 18 to 90 with a mean age of 51.98.

Sex distribution

The sample had 123 women (50.62%).

Education distribution

The vast majority participants had some college (77.8%).

Race distribution

The samples were almost equally distributed between White (33.7%), Black (33.3%), or Hispanic/Latino (33.7%).

Income distribution

The most frequent income band selected was $40,000-$49,999.

The median income band was $50,000 - $60,000

Employment distribution

The most frequent employment was No, no paid employment: Retired/pension.

28.4% were employeed full time.

29.63% were retired.

Class distribution

The most frequent class was Middle class, 45.68%.
